bioghist.head: ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY
bioghist.p: The Cornell University College of Veterinary Medicine was founded in 1894. It was originally named the New York State College of Veterinary Medicine.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: The collection contains materials relating to the history and founding of the College, administration and various departments including academics, the clinic, and buildings. Included are reports, notes, files, course materials, evaluations, handbooks, building plans, calendars, schedules, newspaper clippings, flyers, sketches, posters, photographs, rosters, sketches, directories, programs, postcards, photographs, slides, films, and guest books.
